# Testing task — Aurika Flow MVP

## Mobile-Centric UI (NEW)
- What: Full mobile-responsive refactor across all pages.
- How: Test on a mobile device or Chrome DevTools mobile emulator (iPhone 14/Pixel 7).
- Use cases:
  - **Bottom Tab Bar**: 8 navigation icons appear at the bottom of the screen on mobile (<768px). Active tab highlighted. Tapping navigates between pages. Bar respects safe-area-inset-bottom.
  - **Header**: Compact single-row header at top of screen (sticky). Shows page title + notification bell + profile avatar. Brand name "Aurika Flow" hidden on mobile to save space.
  - **Dashboard**: KPI cards display in 2-column grid. Mini stats row scrolls horizontally. Main content grid stacks to single column. Tables shrink font sizes.
  - **Orders/Purchases (list-detail)**: On mobile, shows list view by default. Tapping an order navigates to full-screen detail view with "← Back" button. "+ New" button opens create form with back button. Cancel returns to list. Form inputs are 44px+ touch targets.
  - **Contacts**: Same list-detail mobile pattern as orders. Tapping a contact shows full-screen detail with back button. Activity and ledger tabs work.
  - **Inventory**: Table hidden on mobile, replaced with card-per-product layout showing Name, SKU, Price, Cost, Stock, Value in a 2×2 grid.
  - **Ledger**: Desktop table hidden on mobile. Transaction cards show contact, reference+date, amount+type badge. Balance cards show contact + balance amount. Tabs are touch-friendly (44px height).
  - **Reports**: Stat cards go 2-column. Report tables shrink text for mobile. Single-column layout.
  - **Login**: Already mobile-friendly, verify centered card renders well on small screens.
  - **Settings**: Verify tag management and notification settings are usable on mobile.
  - **Touch targets**: All buttons, links, selects are at least 44px on touch devices.
  - **No horizontal scroll**: Body doesn't scroll horizontally on any page.
  - **iOS input zoom prevention**: Inputs render at 16px font to prevent auto-zoom.

## Dashboard
- What: Overview stats (Total Orders, Total Purchases, Inventory value, Outstanding balance).
- How: Open `/` (Dashboard). Verify stat cards load with data from dummy data.
- Use cases:
  - Four stat cards render with correct values from seed data.
  - No errors or loading spinners stuck.

## Orders page
- What: Split-pane order list + order detail. Create order form.
- How: Open `/orders`. Click order rows. Click "+ New" to create.
- Use cases:
  - Left pane shows list of orders with ID, customer name, total.
  - Clicking an order shows detail: customer, date, items table (product, qty, price, total), order total.
  - "+ New" opens create form with customer dropdown (shows only customers, not suppliers).
  - Product picker shows product name + price.
  - Creating an order adds it to the list, reduces inventory stock, adds a ledger debit entry.
  - After creating, invalidating queries refreshes Orders, Inventory, and Ledger data.

## Inventory page
- What: Product table showing stock and value.
- How: Open `/inventory`. Review table.
- Use cases:
  - Table has columns: Name, SKU, Price, Cost, Stock, Value.
  - Value = stock × costPrice per row.
  - Data loads from seed products.

## Purchases page
