## Zoho account selection
- What: Select which Zoho inbox to manage when multiple accounts are available.
- How: Connect Zoho in `Settings > Email` using a login with multiple accounts; choose an inbox and complete sync.
- Use cases:
  - OAuth success with multiple accounts shows a selection list.
  - Confirming a selection saves the integration and syncs with the chosen email address.
  - Cancel clears the selection state and returns to provider selection.
  - Single-account logins still connect immediately without prompting.
  - Accounts missing emails allow manual entry; the connect button stays disabled until the email is valid.
  - When a Zoho account exposes multiple addresses, each address appears as a selectable option.

## Email inbox sync + replies
- What: Synced emails appear in the inbox and Zoho replies stay in-thread.
- How: Sync from `Email` page and then reply to a Zoho conversation.
- Use cases:
  - Newly imported emails appear in the inbox within the default 30-day range.
  - Conversation ordering does not regress when older messages are imported.
  - Zoho replies show up in the same thread (not a new conversation).

## Cross-date channel search
- What: Email/WhatsApp/IVR search ignores the date range filter and finds older conversations/calls.
- How: In each channel page, set the date range to a single day with no matches, then search for a known contact/email/phone that exists outside that range.
- Use cases:
  - Email search returns matches even when the selected date range does not include the conversation.
  - WhatsApp search returns matches outside the selected date range.
  - IVR phone search returns calls outside the selected date range and still paginates with Load more.
  - Email search returns matches without requiring a manual "Load more" click when results exist in recent pages.

## Access denied channel pages
- What: Direct navigation to a restricted channel page shows access denied and does not fetch channel data.
- How: Use a user without the module, paste the URL for `/whatsapp`, `/email`, `/ivr`, `/chatbot`.
- Use cases:
  - Access denied card renders in place of the channel UI.
  - Network tab shows no calls to channel inbox/detail endpoints for the restricted page.
  - No loading spinners keep running on restricted pages.

## Access denied contacts/tickets
- What: Direct navigation to `/contacts` and `/tickets` respects module access and backend denies requests.
